nbk -> number of banks per memory partition
nbkgrp -> number of bank groups
CCD -> column-to-column delay (same bank group)
CCDL -> column-to-column delay (different bank group)
RRD -> row-to-row activation delay (between two ACT commands)
RCD -> row-to-column delay (ACT to READ/WRITE)
RAS -> row active time (minimum time a row must remain open)
RP -> row precharge time (time to close a row before opening another)
RC -> row cycle time (total time between two ACTs to same bank, RC = RAS + RP)
CL -> CAS latency (delay from READ command to data availability)
WL -> write latency (delay from WRITE command to data acceptance)
CDLR -> bus turnaround delay (WRITE to READ)
WR -> write recovery time (time from end of WRITE to PRECHARGE)
RTPL -> read-to-precharge latency (delay from READ completion to PRECHARGE)


